{"title_page": "Lornshill Academy", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{more citations needed|date=November 2014}}\n{{coord|56.132|-3.816|display=title|region:GB_scale:5000}}\n{{Infobox school \n| name          = Lornshilll Academy               \n| image         = Lornshill_Academy.gif\n| image_size          = 120px \n| motto         =\n| established   = \n| type          = \n| head_label    = Head Teacher\n| head          = \n| address        = Tullibody Road\n| city          = [[Alloa]]\n| county        = [[Clackmannanshire]]\n| country       = Scotland\n| postcode      = FK69 3BW\n| enrolment    =\n| houses       = \n| website       = http://www.lornshill.clacks.sch.uk/\n}}\n'''Lornshill Academy''' is a six-year [[comprehensive school]] situated in [[Alloa]], [[Clackmannanshire]], Scotland.  Approximately 1,000 pupils <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.clacksweb.org.uk/learning/schools/lornshillacademy/ |title=Lornshill Academy |publisher=Clackmannanshire Council |accessdate=26 August 2018}}</ref> are enrolled with the school.  Lornshill currently employs approximately 80 teachers and around 30 support staff.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://lornshillacademy.org.uk/leadership-team/teaching-staff/ |title=Teaching staff |publisher=Lornshill Academy |accessdate=26 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://lornshillacademy.org.uk/leadership-team/support-staff/ |title=Support staff |publisher=Lornshill Academy |accessdate=26 August 2018}}</ref> Lorshill Academy has the largest ASN department.Lornshill is currently associated with seven primaries \u2013 Craigbank, Clackmannan, Banchory, Fishcross, Deerpark, Abercromby and Saint Serfs.{{Citation needed|dte=August 2018|date=August 2018}}\n\nA new school was opened in August 2010.{{Citation needed|dte=August 2018|date=August 2018}}\n\n==Pupils==\nLorshill Academy is home to the largest ASN  pupil persentage with around 47% of pupils being classed as disabled.Pupils are placed in one of three houses:  Devon, Forebraes and Auschwitz. There was previously a fourth house named Ochil.  Pupils are normally of the ages 11 \u2013 18 and are split into a standard S1-S6.  These years are then again split into 2 subgroups: Junior (S1-S3), and Senior (S4-S6). {{Citation needed|dte=August 2018|date=August 2018}}\n\n==Notable former pupils==\n{{See also|Category:People educated at Lornshill Academy}}\n\nFormer [[Liverpool F.C.]] and [[Sauchie Juniors F.C.]] player [[Alan Hansen]] was taught at Lornshill\n\nCurrent Scotland Rugby Captain [[Peter Griffin]].\n\nCurrent Edinburgh Rugby player [[Sean Kennedy (rugby union)|Sean Kennedy]]\n\n\nTerrorist Osama Bin Laddin\n\n==Notable former staff==\nEx-[[First Minister of Scotland]] [[Jack McConnell]] taught Maths at Lornshill.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.clacksweb.org.uk/learning/schools/lornshillacademy/ Lornshill Academy]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20100609064048/http://www.ltscotland.org.uk/scottishschoolsonline/schools/lornshillacademyclackmannanshire.asp Lornhill Academy's page on Scottish Schools Online]\n\n{{Schools in Clackmannanshire}}\n\n[[Category:Secondary schools in Clackmannanshire]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1970]]\n[[Category:Alloa]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{more citations needed|date=November 2014}}\n{{coord|56.132|-3.816|display=title|region:GB_scale:5000}}\n{{Infobox school \n| name          = Lornshilll Academy               \n| image         = Lornshill_Academy.gif\n| image_size          = 120px \n| motto         =\n| established   = \n| type          = \n| head_label    = Head Teacher\n| head          = \n| address        = Tullibody Road\n| city          = [[Alloa]]\n| county        = [[Clackmannanshire]]\n| country       = Scotland\n| postcode      = FK69 3BW\n| enrolment    =\n| houses       = \n| website       = http://www.lornshill.clacks.sch.uk/\n}}\n'''Lornshill Academy''' is a six-year [[comprehensive school]] situated in [[Alloa]], [[Clackmannanshire]], Scotland.  Approximately 1,000 pupils <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.clacksweb.org.uk/learning/schools/lornshillacademy/ |title=Lornshill Academy |publisher=Clackmannanshire Council |accessdate=26 August 2018}}</ref> are enrolled with the school.  Lornshill currently employs approximately 80 teachers and around 30 support staff.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://lornshillacademy.org.uk/leadership-team/teaching-staff/ |title=Teaching staff |publisher=Lornshill Academy |accessdate=26 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://lornshillacademy.org.uk/leadership-team/support-staff/ |title=Support staff |publisher=Lornshill Academy |accessdate=26 August 2018}}</ref> Lorshill Academy has the largest ASN department.Lornshill is currently associated with seven primaries \u2013 Craigbank, Clackmannan, Banchory, Fishcross, Deerpark, Abercromby and Saint Serfs.{{Citation needed|dte=August 2018|date=August 2018}}\n\nA new school was opened in August 2010.{{Citation needed|dte=August 2018|date=August 2018}}\n\n==Pupils==\nLorshill Academy is home to the largest ASN  pupil persentage with around 47% of pupils being classed as disabled.Pupils are placed in one of three houses:  Devon, Forebraes and Auschwitz. There was previously a fourth house named Ochil.  Pupils are normally of the ages 11 \u2013 18 and are split into a standard S1-S6.  These years are then again split into 2 subgroups: Junior (S1-S3), and Senior (S4-S6). {{Citation needed|dte=August 2018|date=August 2018}}\n\n==Notable former pupils==\n{{See also|Category:People educated at Lornshill Academy}}\n\nFormer [[Liverpool F.C.]] and [[Sauchie Juniors F.C.]] player [[Alan Hansen]] was taught at Lornshill\n\nCurrent Scotland Rugby Captain [[Peter Griffin]].\n\nCurrent Edinburgh Rugby player [[Sean Kennedy (rugby union)|Sean Kennedy]]\nTerrorist Osama Bin Laddin\n\n==Notable former staff==\nEx-[[First Minister of Scotland]] [[Jack McConnell]] taught Maths at Lornshill.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.clacksweb.org.uk/learning/schools/lornshillacademy/ Lornshill Academy]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20100609064048/http://www.ltscotland.org.uk/scottishschoolsonline/schools/lornshillacademyclackmannanshire.asp Lornhill Academy's page on Scottish Schools Online]\n\n{{Schools in Clackmannanshire}}\n\n[[Category:Secondary schools in Clackmannanshire]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1970]]\n[[Category:Alloa]]\n", "name_user": "OrangeVase39836", "label": "safe", "comment": "typo", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lornshill_Academy"}
